00:20:44,330 --> 00:20:45,374
I don't know.

274
00:20:46,832 --> 00:20:48,838
Maybe you told her not to?

275
00:20:49,043 --> 00:20:51,677
I thought we had a real talk.

276
00:20:53,965 --> 00:20:55,092
Do you like

277
00:20:55,967 --> 00:20:59,265
this motorcycle instructor
she hangs out with?

278
00:20:59,428 --> 00:21:02,477
Whether I do or not,
it's her business now.

279
00:21:02,682 --> 00:21:07,071
Encourage her to date a guy
who sells used cars from Germany!

280
00:21:07,270 --> 00:21:09,156
He doesn't sell them.

281
00:21:09,355 --> 00:21:12,404
He just brought over
a bike for himself.

282
00:21:12,608 --> 00:21:13,570
Yes, right.

283
00:21:14,110 --> 00:21:16,364
Want me to pick her boyfriends?

284
00:21:16,571 --> 00:21:18,161
Let her experience life.

285
00:21:18,364 --> 00:21:23,288
Nowadays you don't have to marry
the first guy you hold hands with.

286
00:21:23,494 --> 00:21:26,591
As if I was
the first you held hands with.

287
00:21:26,956 --> 00:21:29,720
Relax, I wasn't thinking of you.

288
00:21:30,501 --> 00:21:33,301
Not everything's about you,
you know.

289
00:21:35,881 --> 00:21:38,100
I'll pack her school lunch.

290
00:21:38,593 --> 00:21:41,096
Should she sit the exam tomorrow?

291
00:21:41,387 --> 00:21:42,858
Of course.

292
00:21:43,472 --> 00:21:46,936
You think this is something
you just shake oft?

293
00:21:47,143 --> 00:21:50,939
Magda! Her scholarship depends on it!
Be responsible!

294
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:55,573
I am, but it's not like
today didn't happen. It happened.

295
00:21:55,776 --> 00:21:59,620
She can't throw away
all her work because of an accident.

296
00:21:59,822 --> 00:22:02,326
Accident?
So rape is an accident?

297
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:05,997
He didn't rape her!
Stop saying that, all of you!

298
00:22:06,203 --> 00:22:07,710
He just forced his head...

299
00:22:07,914 --> 00:22:08,708
Stop it!

300
00:22:08,915 --> 00:22:11,632
She'll sit the exam,
and that's final!

301
00:22:22,053 --> 00:22:24,224
It's time to let her decide.

302
00:22:24,430 --> 00:22:28,061
I will. And she'll agree,
you'll see.

303
00:22:28,267 --> 00:22:29,904
Just don't meddle.

304
00:22:30,895 --> 00:22:32,817
Could you two keep it down?

305
00:22:33,773 --> 00:22:35,825
Where are your socks?

306
00:22:39,445 --> 00:22:40,656
Eliza.

307
00:22:41,614 --> 00:22:45,410
Tomorrow I'll see
if we can postpone the exam.

308
00:22:45,826 --> 00:22:49,338
But if we can't,
you have to do your best.

309
00:22:50,456 --> 00:22:52,461
I don't know if I can write.

310
00:22:52,833 --> 00:22:56,511
Everybody will be nice to you.
They'll understand.

311
00:23:02,218 --> 00:23:04,270
I'm going to bed now.

312
00:25:48,050 --> 00:25:49,224
Excuse me, madam!

313
00:25:49,594 --> 00:25:50,768
Madam!

314
00:25:52,638 --> 00:25:53,812
Good morning.

315
00:25:54,098 --> 00:25:57,277
I have to talk to an exam supervisor.

316
00:25:57,518 --> 00:25:59,404
But the guards here claim...

317
00:25:59,604 --> 00:26:02,902
- Parents are not allowed.
- It's fine, don't worry.

318
00:26:03,107 --> 00:26:05,408
There are rules-

319
00:26:05,610 --> 00:26:09,073
Don't worry, I'll handle it!

320
00:26:14,201 --> 00:26:17,416
Doctor,
I agree it's a prestigious university,

321
00:26:17,622 --> 00:26:19,923
but the regulations state that-

322
00:26:20,124 --> 00:26:23,339
Mr. President.
Do they state "no casts allowed"?

323
00:26:23,586 --> 00:26:26,386
We have to rule out
all possible fraud.

324
00:26:26,589 --> 00:26:29,436
Her final high school average was 9.5!

325
00:26:29,634 --> 00:26:34,640
Yes but last year we had a good student
with notes in his plaster.

326
00:26:34,847 --> 00:26:37,351
Isn't it a case-by-case decision?

327
00:26:37,558 --> 00:26:39,610
Yes, but the procedure-

328
00:26:39,810 --> 00:26:42,528
She was attacked
in front of the school!

329
00:26:42,730 --> 00:26:45,530
Not in the school
so it's not our fault!

330
00:26:45,733 --> 00:26:47,820
It's never the school's fault, is it?

331
00:26:48,027 --> 00:26:51,491
Doctor, we're deeply sorry,
but the rules-

332
00:26:51,739 --> 00:26:54,587
Please just allow her to sit the exam!

333
00:26:54,784 --> 00:26:57,963
Let the board decide
if she's to be disqualified.

334
00:26:58,246 --> 00:27:00,416
But please give her a chance!

335
00:27:01,749 --> 00:27:05,546
Send her in.
And let's hope we get no complaints.

336
00:27:05,753 --> 00:27:09,550
You won't.
Thank you, I'm in your debt.

337
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:12,143
Let's go.

338
00:28:11,193 --> 00:28:14,123
- Did you bring my results?
- There.

339
00:28:14,822 --> 00:28:18,286
They changed your medication.
You're on Cavinton now.

340
00:28:19,493 --> 00:28:21,581
For a month, then we'll see.

341
00:28:23,664 --> 00:28:24,542
Wait...

342
00:28:25,958 --> 00:28:27,346
There's a page missing?

343
00:28:27,543 --> 00:28:31,600
Really, Mum, don't you trust me?

344
00:28:33,007 --> 00:28:35,427
Here. Take this when you go.

345
00:28:35,635 --> 00:28:36,726
What's this?

346
00:28:37,053 --> 00:28:40,399
The photo album.
I found it in the cabinet.

347
00:28:41,265 --> 00:28:42,986
Don't you want to keep it?

348
00:28:43,309 --> 00:28:45,396
Eliza may want it, when she leaves.

349
00:28:45,728 --> 00:28:47,448
There are photos of her.

350
00:28:49,106 --> 00:28:50,150
Fine.

351
00:28:51,442 --> 00:28:54,788
But calm down,
Pandele told you to rest.

352
00:28:54,987 --> 00:28:57,039
You turned the house upside down.

353
00:28:57,239 --> 00:29:00,288
Because I forgot where it was,
that's why.

354
00:29:01,702 --> 00:29:02,960
Fine, fine.

355
00:29:03,287 --> 00:29:05,968
Eliza said she'd stop by, yesterday,

356
00:29:06,165 --> 00:29:08,301
to take up her party dress.

357
00:29:08,751 --> 00:29:12,844
Mum, she's busy with the exams,
with going away...

358
00:29:15,549 --> 00:29:18,515
Don't open for anyone,
some convicts escaped.

359
00:29:18,761 --> 00:29:20,517
It was on the radio.

360
00:29:22,390 --> 00:29:26,530
I don't agree with her leaving,
not one bit.

361
00:29:26,769 --> 00:29:28,323
So what should we do?

362
00:29:29,272 --> 00:29:30,909
You say that now,

363
00:29:31,107 --> 00:29:34,903
but do you know the feeling,
when your child leaves?

364
00:29:35,444 --> 00:29:38,374
I understand, Mum,
but it's for her sake.

365
00:29:38,572 --> 00:29:40,993
What if she studied here in Cluj?

366
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:43,751
What's there for her here, Mum?

367
00:29:43,953 --> 00:29:45,460
What's so terrible about here?

368
00:29:45,663 --> 00:29:47,585
She has her home,

369
00:29:47,790 --> 00:29:51,551
she has you.
She'd be nearby, you'd have each other.

370
00:29:52,128 --> 00:29:55,011
Everything is difficult here,
you need to-

371
00:29:55,256 --> 00:29:58,020
Do you think
it's any different elsewhere?

372
00:29:59,176 --> 00:30:03,483
She should stay and change things!
If they all leave...

373
00:30:03,681 --> 00:30:07,228
We stayed and what did we change,
in the end?

374
00:30:07,935 --> 00:30:10,403
You changed what could be changed.

375
00:30:10,605 --> 00:30:13,025
There, you don't need connections.

376
00:30:13,232 --> 00:30:15,569
She's not the type to tough it out.

377
00:30:15,776 --> 00:30:17,497
And after we're gone...

378
00:30:18,571 --> 00:30:23,080
It's because you babied her.
She's never had to face trouble.

379
00:30:23,284 --> 00:30:25,965
We had our own share of trouble
already.

380
00:30:26,412 --> 00:30:28,132
I should go now.

381
00:30:28,331 --> 00:30:29,754
Anything else you need?

382
00:30:29,957 --> 00:30:33,303
I told you before, but you forgot.

383
00:30:33,502 --> 00:30:34,464
What?

384
00:30:35,546 --> 00:30:38,310
Clear the grass from the grave.

385
00:30:38,758 --> 00:30:42,020
And pour some concrete,
it's cleaner.

386
00:30:42,219 --> 00:30:43,560
Really, Mum...

387
00:30:43,763 --> 00:30:45,850
Please, do it for me.

388
00:30:46,933 --> 00:30:48,735
I can't do it myself anymore.

389
00:30:49,101 --> 00:30:50,774
Fine, I'll see.

390
00:30:51,896 --> 00:30:53,403
You said that already.

391
00:30:53,648 --> 00:30:55,487
I won't forget. Bye.

392
00:30:55,733 --> 00:30:57,204
Take care.

393
00:31:00,947 --> 00:31:02,418
- Lock the door!
- I will.

394
00:31:26,222 --> 00:31:27,432
How is Eliza doing?

395
00:31:27,932 --> 00:31:29,059
So-so.

396
00:31:30,142 --> 00:31:31,779
Thanks for this morning.

397
00:31:31,978 --> 00:31:33,780
That guy's an idiot.

398
00:31:34,563 --> 00:31:36,403
Good thing it worked out.

399
00:31:36,983 --> 00:31:38,988
For her scholarship, she needs...

400
00:31:39,193 --> 00:31:41,329
At least a 9. On average.

401
00:31:45,199 --> 00:31:46,410
This is so stupid.

402
00:31:53,791 --> 00:31:54,669
What?

403
00:31:55,835 --> 00:31:56,796
Nothing.

404
00:31:57,837 --> 00:31:59,178
Tell me.

405
00:32:01,340 --> 00:32:04,270
It's nothing.
My period is 6 days late.

406
00:32:10,266 --> 00:32:11,654
Why that face?

407
00:32:12,435 --> 00:32:13,692
What face?

408
00:32:14,478 --> 00:32:15,440
That one.

409
00:32:16,397 --> 00:32:17,785
I wasn't expecting it.

410
00:32:22,194 --> 00:32:24,081
Why not?

411
00:32:25,156 --> 00:32:27,042
Shall we talk now?

412
00:32:27,700 --> 00:32:29,787
You seem a bit tense.

413
00:32:33,039 --> 00:32:35,008
Good thing you're so calm.

414
00:32:36,334 --> 00:32:37,544
Isn't that Matei?

415
00:32:39,462 --> 00:32:40,636
Yes.

416
00:32:41,255 --> 00:32:43,260
I couldn't leave him home alone.

417
00:32:43,466 --> 00:32:44,509
I'll be off.

418
00:33:07,573 --> 00:33:08,961
Yes, Magda.

419
00:33:09,533 --> 00:33:11,835
She's out, she's with me.

420
00:33:12,912 --> 00:33:14,715
She just got out.

421
00:33:16,249 --> 00:33:19,214
She did well
on what she could finish.

422
00:33:19,418 --> 00:33:21,720
She didn't do the last two questions.

423
00:33:22,630 --> 00:33:23,971
No, not at all.

424
00:33:25,091 --> 00:33:26,977
She just didn't have time.

425
00:33:28,511 --> 00:33:30,314
You can talk to her at home.

426
00:33:33,057 --> 00:33:34,445
Would you talk to Mum?

427
00:33:40,815 --> 00:33:42,950
Mum, I'll call you later, OK?

428
00:33:44,652 --> 00:33:46,242
No, nothing hurts.

429
00:33:48,489 --> 00:33:50,079
I knew the answers but...

430
00:33:50,741 --> 00:33:51,833
I don't know.

431
00:33:53,327 --> 00:33:55,048
No, that wasn't it.

432
00:33:59,041 --> 00:34:01,924
I call you a bit later, Mum,
OK?

433
00:34:04,714 --> 00:34:07,644
Calm down,
it's not the end of the world.

434
00:34:08,926 --> 00:34:10,729
We'll manage, don't worry.

435
00:34:14,098 --> 00:34:15,688
Shall I drive you home?

436
00:34:15,933 --> 00:34:17,570
No, I'm meeting Marius.

437
00:34:18,769 --> 00:34:20,359
Is that a good idea?

438
00:34:20,855 --> 00:34:22,527
I promised.

439
00:34:36,829 --> 00:34:37,837
Thanks.

440
00:34:44,587 --> 00:34:45,844
Sandu!

441
00:34:46,255 --> 00:34:47,299
<i>Yes, Iâ€œ?

442
00:34:47,506 --> 00:34:49,843
- The doctor's here.
- I'm coming.

443
00:34:52,136 --> 00:34:53,643
What are these for?

444
00:34:54,555 --> 00:34:56,394
I had this breakdown...

445
00:34:56,599 --> 00:34:57,940
Because of the divorce?

446
00:34:59,143 --> 00:35:00,733
Maybe.
No idea.

447
00:35:00,937 --> 00:35:03,902
I panicked.
I'd made a mess of my life...

448
00:35:04,106 --> 00:35:05,578
I'd wasted it...

449
00:35:05,983 --> 00:35:10,373
So I went to a doctor
who told me to get these marbles.

450
00:35:10,947 --> 00:35:14,293
Here's one for each day I've lived

451
00:35:14,492 --> 00:35:15,915
and here, there's one

452
00:35:16,285 --> 00:35:19,631
for each day until I retire,

453
00:35:19,830 --> 00:35:22,714
at 65,
unless they change the law again.

454
00:35:23,125 --> 00:35:27,218
So every evening I move one marble
and think a bit.

455
00:35:27,546 --> 00:35:29,516
Was he a doctor or a priest?

456
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:33,269
A doctor but you know,
that kind of doctor...

457
00:35:34,470 --> 00:35:36,309
The marking scheme for Romanian.

458
00:35:36,681 --> 00:35:38,567
Well done, Sandu!

459
00:35:38,933 --> 00:35:40,736
- One more task.
- Please.

460
00:35:40,935 --> 00:35:45,823
The good doctor here noticed
a surveillance camera at the comer.

461
00:35:46,023 --> 00:35:47,316
- By the school?
- Yes.

462
00:35:47,525 --> 00:35:49,779
Solved. The recording comes today.

463
00:35:49,986 --> 00:35:51,409
Bravo, Sandu.

464
00:35:52,238 --> 00:35:54,160
- Anything else?
- That's all.

465
00:35:54,365 --> 00:35:55,243
Thank you, sir.

466
00:35:59,996 --> 00:36:01,383
Let's see...

467
00:36:02,415 --> 00:36:06,092
3.2 for the character description.

468
00:36:06,294 --> 00:36:10,220
2.5 for the vocabulary section...
say 2, she didn't finish it...

469
00:36:10,548 --> 00:36:12,683
1.5 for the predicative clause...

470
00:36:12,883 --> 00:36:15,469
My daughter will get a 1,
and Eliza...

471
00:36:15,678 --> 00:36:18,478
- Minus the last 2 questions.
- 8...

472
00:36:20,558 --> 00:36:23,607
- It's the right breakdown?
- Certainly.

473
00:36:24,687 --> 00:36:25,814
Not good, then.

474
00:36:26,022 --> 00:36:28,786
She'd need straight tens
in the next tests.

475
00:36:28,983 --> 00:36:30,620
I believe she can do it.

476
00:36:32,737 --> 00:36:34,706
The September session, maybe?

477
00:36:35,197 --> 00:36:37,203
Too late, I checked.

478
00:36:38,576 --> 00:36:41,375
- You should talk to Bulai.
- About what?

479
00:36:41,746 --> 00:36:43,087
You called about his liver?

480
00:36:43,289 --> 00:36:45,341
Boghean called me yesterday.

481
00:36:45,541 --> 00:36:48,127
Even better. Ask Bulai.
He can help.

482
00:36:48,294 --> 00:36:50,548
What can he do about this?

483
00:36:50,963 --> 00:36:52,351
Want me to call him?

484
00:36:53,049 --> 00:36:54,259
I'll do it.

485
00:37:05,478 --> 00:37:08,242
Hello, sir! How are you doing?

486
00:37:09,941 --> 00:37:13,073
Also busy.
My daughter's doing her final exams.

487
00:37:13,444 --> 00:37:14,867
Yes, thank you.

488
00:37:15,279 --> 00:37:17,616
I have news.
Good news, hopefully.

489
00:37:17,907 --> 00:37:21,253
My friend put in a word
about the transplant.

490
00:37:21,452 --> 00:37:23,374
And we're hoping...

491
00:37:23,621 --> 00:37:25,341
for a positive answer.

492
00:37:26,791 --> 00:37:29,638
It might take a while.
They need a donor first...

493
00:37:30,294 --> 00:37:32,595
Of course we'll let you know,

494
00:37:32,797 --> 00:37:34,387
the good Lord willing.

495
00:37:34,632 --> 00:37:36,103
I have a question, sir.

496
00:37:36,300 --> 00:37:40,310
Could you help Dr. Aldea?
He has a problem.

497
00:37:41,555 --> 00:37:45,778
His daughter narrowly escaped
being raped right by the school.

498
00:37:46,060 --> 00:37:48,610
So she couldn't focus too well

499
00:37:48,813 --> 00:37:51,447
for the written Romanian test today.

500
00:37:51,857 --> 00:37:55,369
She's very good,
she got a scholarship to Cambridge...

501
00:37:55,611 --> 00:37:58,328
But it depends on her results.

502
00:37:59,907 --> 00:38:02,588
He's here with me,
he can tell you more.

503
00:38:03,577 --> 00:38:05,084
Have a good day.

504
00:38:06,539 --> 00:38:08,959
He'll wait for you at 6,
in his office.

505
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:13,382
Romeo, it's for your child!

506
00:38:14,547 --> 00:38:15,935
Write down his number.

507
00:39:12,897 --> 00:39:12,979
- A bit more?
- I don't drink often.

508
00:39:12,980 --> 00:39:15,448
- A bit more?
- I don't drink often.

509
00:39:15,733 --> 00:39:17,820
Me, I haven't touched alcohol

510
00:39:18,027 --> 00:39:20,495
for exactly a year and 6 months!

511
00:39:21,113 --> 00:39:24,708
But it's too late.
My liver still won't regenerate.

512
00:39:25,034 --> 00:39:26,457
And your test results?

513
00:39:26,661 --> 00:39:29,591
Bad. I haven't done any recently.
Got scared.

514
00:39:29,789 --> 00:39:31,082
You should do them.

515
00:39:31,707 --> 00:39:34,555
Let's get you admitted
for tests tomorrow.

516
00:39:34,752 --> 00:39:36,306
If you say so.

517
00:39:36,671 --> 00:39:41,310
A liver could show up any day,
but if you're not ready...

518
00:39:41,509 --> 00:39:44,439
You've convinced me!
See how easy it was?

519
00:39:44,804 --> 00:39:46,357
Tell me straight:

520
00:39:46,681 --> 00:39:48,353
Is it a difficult operation?

521
00:39:48,683 --> 00:39:51,945
Yes. The body needs
to accept the foreign organ.

522
00:39:52,561 --> 00:39:53,605
In other words,

523
00:39:54,230 --> 00:39:56,780
the first 24 hours are crucial.

524
00:39:57,149 --> 00:39:58,656
Don't scare me.

525
00:39:59,026 --> 00:40:02,870
I won't, but you have responsibilities,
a family...

526
00:40:03,322 --> 00:40:06,419
You need to know the situation
before surgery.

527
00:40:06,617 --> 00:40:11,457
Oh, you're the kind of doctor
who tells his patient the truth.

528
00:40:11,747 --> 00:40:13,254
In your case, yes.

529
00:40:13,624 --> 00:40:16,590
In my mother's case, it's pointless.

530
00:40:16,794 --> 00:40:18,799
- What's wrong with her?
- Nothing.

531
00:40:19,505 --> 00:40:21,261
But at her age...

532
00:40:21,716 --> 00:40:23,472
So how long do you think

533
00:40:23,676 --> 00:40:26,144
we'll wait for the healthy organ?

534
00:40:26,512 --> 00:40:30,356
It can take years,
or it can happen very quickly.

535
00:40:30,641 --> 00:40:32,231
It depends on donors...

536
00:40:32,435 --> 00:40:35,532
I see.
In any case, I'm ready.

537
00:40:35,938 --> 00:40:38,074
I have my testament, the money...

538
00:40:38,274 --> 00:40:40,160
Money won't be an issue.

539
00:40:40,526 --> 00:40:44,583
Come on, doctor,
don't tell me you live off your salary!

540
00:40:44,780 --> 00:40:46,417
That's not it.

541
00:40:47,867 --> 00:40:51,829
I hope you don't think you owe me
for helping your daughter.

542
00:40:52,038 --> 00:40:55,834
You can't compare a man's life
with some exam. An exam...

543
00:40:56,334 --> 00:40:59,845
I've called Serban,
the exam board chief.

544
00:41:00,171 --> 00:41:03,268
He understood the situation.
He's a nice man, you know...

545
00:41:03,549 --> 00:41:05,886
He came to me once with a problem.

546
00:41:06,218 --> 00:41:08,722
His wife was fired
from the town hall.

547
00:41:08,930 --> 00:41:11,433
They cut jobs
while she was pregnant.

548
00:41:11,807 --> 00:41:13,398
I got her back in.

549
00:41:13,768 --> 00:41:16,900
He's been very grateful to me
ever since.

550
00:41:17,188 --> 00:41:20,700
Who'll take you on again at 43?

551
00:41:21,442 --> 00:41:23,281
People should help each other.

552
00:41:23,694 --> 00:41:27,372
My position won me many enemies,

553
00:41:27,615 --> 00:41:30,332
but also many friends!

554
00:41:31,327 --> 00:41:33,047
Could I have another drop?

555
00:41:34,580 --> 00:41:36,170
Good, isn't it?

556
00:41:48,010 --> 00:41:49,221
Is something wrong?

557
00:41:49,512 --> 00:41:50,686
No. Why?

558
00:41:50,888 --> 00:41:52,774
You're here? At this hour?

559
00:41:53,849 --> 00:41:56,400
I wanted to say sorry for earlier.

560
00:42:03,192 --> 00:42:04,663
The neighbors are watching.

561
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:06,284
So what?

562
00:42:07,321 --> 00:42:08,709
How's Eliza?

563
00:42:09,448 --> 00:42:10,706
Not good.

564
00:42:11,117 --> 00:42:12,410
She didn't do well.

565
00:42:12,576 --> 00:42:14,214
- On her test?
- Yes.

566
00:42:16,205 --> 00:42:17,297
I'm sorry.

567
00:42:17,790 --> 00:42:18,668
Yes.

568
00:42:20,209 --> 00:42:22,095
I wanted to ask you.

569
00:42:22,545 --> 00:42:26,851
Could they let her write
a bit more once the 3 hours are up?

570
00:42:27,717 --> 00:42:29,104
Not really.

571
00:42:30,177 --> 00:42:30,972
I see.

572
00:42:32,555 --> 00:42:35,604
Well, then I don't know.
We'll see.

573
00:42:39,478 --> 00:42:40,866
<i>'Ms is Mam.

574
00:42:42,273 --> 00:42:45,073
Dr. Aldea, who operated on Mum...

575
00:42:45,651 --> 00:42:47,039
Hello, Matei.

576
00:42:48,654 --> 00:42:51,074
Matei, will you take that mask off?

577
00:42:52,658 --> 00:42:53,785
Let him be.

578
00:42:54,368 --> 00:42:55,958
I'll be going.

579
00:42:56,162 --> 00:42:57,336
Bye, Matei.

580
00:43:04,045 --> 00:43:06,381
Do you mind that I introduced you?

581
00:43:06,589 --> 00:43:08,345
No, why should I?

582
00:43:08,924 --> 00:43:10,680
You didn't want to meet him.

583
00:43:11,218 --> 00:43:12,476
You didn't want it.

584
00:43:13,971 --> 00:43:16,735
But now I thought you should meet.

585
00:43:17,266 --> 00:43:18,393
So we've met.

586
00:43:19,602 --> 00:43:21,109
I have to go.

587
00:43:22,521 --> 00:43:23,565
Go, then.

588
00:43:48,756 --> 00:43:50,642
The light attracts the moths.

589
00:43:50,841 --> 00:43:52,229
Don't worry.

590
00:43:52,426 --> 00:43:54,930
- Do you want some cake?
- No, thanks.

591
00:43:55,221 --> 00:43:56,774
Homemade, by my wife.

592
00:43:56,973 --> 00:43:59,938
I've bothered you enough already.

593
00:44:00,268 --> 00:44:01,608
It happens.

594
00:44:02,728 --> 00:44:05,113
Happy birthday to your wife.

595
00:44:05,356 --> 00:44:06,364
I'll tell her.

596
00:44:07,692 --> 00:44:10,325
- Can I get you a chair?
- Don't bother.

597
00:44:11,320 --> 00:44:13,906
Forgive me for this morning.

598
00:44:14,115 --> 00:44:16,084
If I seemed a bit aggressive...

599
00:44:16,284 --> 00:44:17,671
Don't worry.

600
00:44:17,994 --> 00:44:19,963
Now, how may I help you?

601
00:44:20,621 --> 00:44:23,800
Mr. Bulai described the situation,
I believe.

602
00:44:24,250 --> 00:44:25,591
Yes, he did.

603
00:44:26,168 --> 00:44:28,174
What grade does the girl need?

604
00:44:28,629 --> 00:44:30,800
She needs a final average of 9

605
00:44:31,007 --> 00:44:32,560
to get the scholarship.

606
00:44:32,967 --> 00:44:34,604
And on the Romanian test?

607
00:44:34,802 --> 00:44:36,854
We estimate an 8 at most.

608
00:44:37,388 --> 00:44:38,811
Have you spoken to anybody?

609
00:44:39,015 --> 00:44:42,692
For the Romanian test? No.
Could we change anything?

610
00:44:43,269 --> 00:44:45,404
It might be a bit late now.

611
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:49,446
There are teachers
from different schools.

612
00:44:49,734 --> 00:44:54,408
I'm very sorry to involve you.
It's very unpleasant.

613
00:44:54,614 --> 00:44:56,120
Such things happen.

614
00:44:56,407 --> 00:44:58,329
What are her grades in maths?

615
00:44:58,534 --> 00:45:02,627
Her final average
at the end of high school is 9.6.

616
00:45:02,830 --> 00:45:04,123
That's good.

617
00:45:05,291 --> 00:45:07,925
So she could get 10 in the exam.

618
00:45:08,419 --> 00:45:10,341
I think so, yes.

619
00:45:11,797 --> 00:45:14,645
I don't know one of the grading teachers.

620
00:45:14,842 --> 00:45:18,354
The other one was a colleague.
A decent man.

621
00:45:18,554 --> 00:45:20,108
But we need both of them.

622
00:45:20,264 --> 00:45:22,400
I don't know how such things work.

623
00:45:22,600 --> 00:45:27,239
They must give similar grades. If not,
the paper goes to another committee.

624
00:45:27,438 --> 00:45:30,119
- It's better not to.
- I see.

625
00:45:30,441 --> 00:45:31,829
So what's best?

626
00:45:33,110 --> 00:45:35,614
I'll see in the morning

627
00:45:35,947 --> 00:45:39,826
or I'll try taking the paper
to another teacher.

628
00:45:40,034 --> 00:45:42,253
But that's a bit more complicated.

629
00:45:42,662 --> 00:45:44,334
Is that the only way?

630
00:45:44,747 --> 00:45:46,633
Do you know of any other?

631
00:45:47,625 --> 00:45:50,342
Please tell me what I have to do.

632
00:45:50,753 --> 00:45:53,257
- How much I should pay.
- Nothing.

633
00:45:53,506 --> 00:45:56,305
Mr. Bulai helped me,
I help you, that's all.

634
00:45:56,509 --> 00:45:58,680
I'll be greatly in your debt.

635
00:45:59,178 --> 00:46:01,183
Could I compensate you somehow...

636
00:46:01,389 --> 00:46:04,236
Don't worry about it, it's fine.

637
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:06,855
Just make sure the girl

638
00:46:07,061 --> 00:46:08,817
marks her paper clearly.

639
00:46:10,189 --> 00:46:11,862
I need to talk to her?

640
00:46:12,066 --> 00:46:14,153
Yes. She must mark the paper.

641
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:16,697
If we miss it, it's over.

642
00:46:17,196 --> 00:46:18,323
I see.

643
00:46:19,198 --> 00:46:24,288
All she has to do is cross out
<i>3</i> words on the first page, bottom line.

644
00:46:24,537 --> 00:46:25,960
The last <i>3</i> words.

645
00:46:27,581 --> 00:46:28,709
Just like this.

646
00:46:29,500 --> 00:46:31,054
- Understood?
- Yes.

647
00:46:35,548 --> 00:46:37,517
OK. Well, thank you.

648
00:46:37,717 --> 00:46:41,311
I'll go. I've disturbed
your wife's birthday long enough.

649
00:46:41,554 --> 00:46:44,567
Doctor, if you have any doubts,
say so now.

650
00:46:44,724 --> 00:46:47,488
This can only work on trust.

651
00:46:47,727 --> 00:46:50,989
I don't want to end up in the news.
Neither do you.

652
00:46:51,188 --> 00:46:52,909
That won't happen.

653
00:46:53,065 --> 00:46:57,288
One more thing:
I'm doing this for the girl.

654
00:46:57,570 --> 00:47:01,413
She shouldn't pay
because we can't handle our criminals.

655
00:47:02,116 --> 00:47:04,002
But I don't do such things.

656
00:47:04,619 --> 00:47:07,965
This house and all you see here
was earned honestly.

657
00:47:08,247 --> 00:47:09,421
I'm sure.

658
00:47:10,291 --> 00:47:11,762
I don't do such things.

659
00:47:11,959 --> 00:47:13,086
I don't doubt it.

660
00:47:14,879 --> 00:47:17,050
I'll see you out.
Some cake?

661
00:47:17,256 --> 00:47:18,727
No, thank you.

662
00:49:55,581 --> 00:50:00,172
Once she starts on this path,
there's no going back.

663
00:50:00,503 --> 00:50:04,346
You can't just shake it off,
say it's OK and move on.

664
00:50:04,632 --> 00:50:08,179
You know in your heart of hearts
that it's not right.

665
00:50:08,886 --> 00:50:12,149
That's not the path
I want Eliza to take in life.

666
00:50:12,348 --> 00:50:14,068
I'm sure you don't either.

667
00:50:16,811 --> 00:50:21,153
If there was any other way,
I wouldn't even think about it.

668
00:50:22,358 --> 00:50:24,577
She shouldn't be doing this.

669
00:50:26,529 --> 00:50:27,739
Magda.

670
00:50:28,656 --> 00:50:32,002
We raised her knowing
she'd leave here.

671
00:50:32,243 --> 00:50:34,295
What if she misses this chance?

672
00:50:34,495 --> 00:50:37,425
She can't handle life here.

673
00:50:38,082 --> 00:50:39,636
She'll learn.

674
00:50:40,418 --> 00:50:44,594
We were just as unprepared
at her age. We handled it.

675
00:50:44,797 --> 00:50:45,924
Did we?

676
00:50:46,590 --> 00:50:48,560
How did we handle it?

677
00:50:48,884 --> 00:50:51,768
By doing things
we wanted her not to do?

678
00:50:52,638 --> 00:50:55,521
But how could she start off in life

679
00:50:55,725 --> 00:50:58,572
with this burden on her shoulders?

680
00:50:59,020 --> 00:51:00,740
What burden, Magda?

681
00:51:00,938 --> 00:51:03,026
This exam's just a formality.

682
00:51:03,232 --> 00:51:05,617
Everyone cheats in their final exam.

683
00:51:05,985 --> 00:51:07,456
I didn't cheat.

684
00:51:07,778 --> 00:51:09,748
Fine, Magda, you didn't.

685
00:51:10,323 --> 00:51:13,870
Anyway, this exam
makes no difference in the end.

686
00:51:14,118 --> 00:51:16,799
Even what they studied in school
is useless.

687
00:51:17,288 --> 00:51:20,669
All that counts is getting
to a normal world.

688
00:51:20,916 --> 00:51:24,131
How you get there matters too.

689
00:51:24,670 --> 00:51:26,343
It's not fair to-

690
00:51:26,547 --> 00:51:30,937
Being attacked in broad daylight
in a crowded place, is that fair?

691
00:51:31,344 --> 00:51:33,146
You want her to live here?

692
00:51:33,346 --> 00:51:35,849
- It was an accident.
- No, it wasn't!

693
00:51:36,307 --> 00:51:39,653
You ended up in some library
because you were fair!

694
00:51:40,019 --> 00:51:42,783
Sometimes the result
is all that matters.

695
00:51:43,147 --> 00:51:46,160
It's our decision,
she needn't feel guilty.

696
00:51:46,359 --> 00:51:49,989
This isn't something
you can decide for her.

697
00:51:50,237 --> 00:51:51,828
So what's your plan?

698
00:51:53,866 --> 00:51:55,077
I don't know.

699
00:51:55,576 --> 00:51:57,166
You know what annoys me?

700
00:51:58,329 --> 00:52:01,960
That you know
there's no other way.

701
00:52:02,166 --> 00:52:05,014
But you won't take any responsibility,

702
00:52:05,211 --> 00:52:06,931
knowing that I'll fix it.

703
00:52:07,129 --> 00:52:11,720
No, but I'm aware that being fair
comes with a price.

704
00:52:12,009 --> 00:52:13,895
And I was willing to pay it.

705
00:52:14,345 --> 00:52:18,900
You could afford to
because I took care of everything!

706
00:52:19,350 --> 00:52:22,814
I'd pay any price in this situation,
if it was about me.

707
00:52:23,229 --> 00:52:25,649
But I won't have my child pay it.

708
00:52:25,856 --> 00:52:27,447
She's my child, too.

709
00:52:27,775 --> 00:52:28,736
Is she?

710
00:52:29,735 --> 00:52:31,954
Fine, then you go talk to her.

711
00:52:43,082 --> 00:52:43,960
Come in.

712
00:52:47,461 --> 00:52:49,763
Are you all right?

713
00:52:50,172 --> 00:52:53,850
Yes, just reading this synopsis.

714
00:52:57,596 --> 00:52:59,352
How did it go with Marius?

715
00:53:01,475 --> 00:53:02,603
OK.

716
00:53:03,477 --> 00:53:05,317
It'll all pass, you'll see.

717
00:53:07,481 --> 00:53:08,525
Yeah.

718
00:53:10,609 --> 00:53:13,160
When you're in Kensington Gardens,

719
00:53:13,362 --> 00:53:17,075
with all those squirrels chasing you,

720
00:53:17,742 --> 00:53:20,956
the world here will seem so far away,

721
00:53:21,162 --> 00:53:23,926
you'll wonder if it was real.

722
00:53:25,291 --> 00:53:26,501
Don't say that.

723
00:53:29,170 --> 00:53:31,305
Do you think it's easy for us?

724
00:53:32,715 --> 00:53:34,186
But that's life.

725
00:53:35,092 --> 00:53:38,889
Children leave home
and learn to live on their own.

726
00:53:41,349 --> 00:53:44,979
Don't be angry
if I don't do well in the exam tomorrow.

727
00:53:45,686 --> 00:53:46,778
Eliza,

728
00:53:48,397 --> 00:53:52,988
you have to do your best.
It'd be a pity to miss this chance.

729
00:53:55,363 --> 00:53:59,040
Some important steps in life
depend on small things.

730
00:54:00,242 --> 00:54:02,793
And some chances shouldn't be wasted.

731
00:54:04,872 --> 00:54:09,796
You know, in '91,
your Mum and I decided to move back.

732
00:54:10,086 --> 00:54:11,427
It was a bad decision.

733
00:54:12,588 --> 00:54:17,263
We thought things would change,
we thought we'd move mountains.

734
00:54:18,427 --> 00:54:20,100
We didn't move anything.

735
00:54:20,721 --> 00:54:22,608
I have no regrets, though.

736
00:54:23,140 --> 00:54:24,730
At least we tried.

737
00:54:26,352 --> 00:54:29,615
But don't make a mistake now
just because we did.

738
00:54:29,814 --> 00:54:33,871
If you do, it means
we lived for nothing, understand?

739
00:54:42,702 --> 00:54:43,829
What's that?

740
00:54:46,330 --> 00:54:49,178
A precaution for tomorrow's exam.

741
00:54:50,418 --> 00:54:54,724
You need to do your best.
I'm sure this won't be necessary.

742
00:54:54,922 --> 00:54:56,761
But we can't risk

743
00:54:56,966 --> 00:55:00,228
you missing this train
for fractions of a point.

744
00:55:04,932 --> 00:55:06,439
I don't understand.

745
00:55:08,394 --> 00:55:12,535
You just have to cross out
<i>3</i> words from the first page.

746
00:55:13,065 --> 00:55:16,613
Just like here.
Regardless of the questions.

747
00:55:17,445 --> 00:55:19,035
Now do you understand?

748
00:55:23,868 --> 00:55:25,256
Eliza...

749
00:55:26,912 --> 00:55:30,376
Sometimes, in life,
it's the result that counts.

750
00:55:31,208 --> 00:55:33,214
Don't get me wrong.

751
00:55:35,087 --> 00:55:38,800
We raised you to always be honest.

752
00:55:39,717 --> 00:55:41,852
But this is the world we live in.

753
00:55:42,261 --> 00:55:46,058
And sometimes we need to fight
using their weapons.

754
00:55:47,725 --> 00:55:52,281
So this is a precaution
that gets you where you want to go,

755
00:55:52,521 --> 00:55:53,993
where you deserve to go.

756
00:55:55,358 --> 00:55:59,534
From there,
you can do what you think is best.

757
00:56:01,322 --> 00:56:03,707
- What I think is best?
- Yes.

758
00:56:04,825 --> 00:56:09,048
Trust me, if there was any way
of changing things here,

759
00:56:09,246 --> 00:56:12,046
I'd urge you to stay and fight.

760
00:56:12,875 --> 00:56:15,556
But it's enough that we stayed.

761
00:56:16,587 --> 00:56:19,684
Let others try too,
we've done our bit.

762
00:56:22,259 --> 00:56:23,731
What does Mum say?

763
00:56:25,388 --> 00:56:29,896
I think she understands
that life has its winners and losers.

764
00:56:30,893 --> 00:56:33,693
And we want you to be a winner.

765
00:56:35,064 --> 00:56:38,528
And have a good life,
since you won't get another.

766
00:56:52,873 --> 00:56:54,961
I'll let you rest now.

767
00:57:02,967 --> 00:57:05,932
Put on some socks.
Don't catch cold.

768
00:57:09,515 --> 00:57:10,856
Goodnight.

769
00:57:13,936 --> 00:57:17,033
You can smoke,
I know you have some there.

770
00:58:12,787 --> 00:58:13,712
Dad?

771
00:58:13,913 --> 00:58:14,874
Yes?

772
00:58:17,375 --> 00:58:19,711
Why do you always beep here?

773
00:58:21,504 --> 00:58:23,057
Just to make sure.

774
00:58:26,050 --> 00:58:28,470
Even when there are no cars?

775
00:58:43,401 --> 00:58:44,528
Want some water?

776
00:58:44,777 --> 00:58:45,536
No.

777
00:58:45,736 --> 00:58:47,290
Did you bring your snack?

778
00:58:47,613 --> 00:58:48,491
Yes.

779
00:58:49,281 --> 00:58:51,750
Eat. It helps the brain.

780
00:59:06,299 --> 00:59:08,635
Good luck. And take care.

781
00:59:11,470 --> 00:59:13,890
- Could you rewind?
- Of course.

782
00:59:19,270 --> 00:59:22,200
A mountain ranger
saw one of the convicts

783
00:59:22,398 --> 00:59:24,368
near the chairlift.

784
00:59:24,567 --> 00:59:26,702
Tomorrow we'll search for him.

785
00:59:28,696 --> 00:59:32,327
That cyclist says he didn't understand
what was going on.

786
00:59:34,285 --> 00:59:36,171
This other one didn't, either?

787
00:59:36,370 --> 00:59:37,842
Every man for himself.

788
00:59:38,664 --> 00:59:40,835
What's the world coming to?

789
00:59:42,043 --> 00:59:43,336
Pause it for a moment!

790
00:59:49,008 --> 00:59:51,476
Can you print me a screenshot?

791
00:59:51,969 --> 00:59:53,227
What for?

792
00:59:53,679 --> 00:59:55,067
Can you?

793
00:59:55,473 --> 00:59:58,687
Sandu, print that
for Lieutenant Bullitt here.

794
00:59:59,018 --> 01:00:00,821
Draw the blinds.

795
01:00:03,147 --> 01:00:04,155
Hello.

796
01:00:04,357 --> 01:00:06,243
- Got the convict?
- Tomorrow.

797
01:00:06,442 --> 01:00:08,245
- Heard about the accident?
- No.

798
01:00:08,444 --> 01:00:11,707
30 minutes ago, by the bridge.
